The article is a statement from the President of the United States regarding the death of Fidel Castro. The President extends condolences to the Cuban people and acknowledges the strong emotions that this moment brings for both Cubans in Cuba and in the United States. The President recognizes the impact that Fidel Castro had on the lives of individuals, families, and the nation of Cuba, and acknowledges that history will judge his role in the world. The President also mentions the discord and political disagreements that have characterized the relationship between the United States and Cuba for nearly six decades. However, during his presidency, efforts have been made to move past these differences and build a future based on shared values and common interests. The President expresses condolences to Castro's family and assures the Cuban people that the United States is a friend and partner.